isks\nwithout fine-tuning the implemented physics. We also show how our model scales\nto smaller systems. By analysing simulations of virial masses 10^9 M_sun/h and\n10^10 M_sun/h, we find that the smaller the galaxy, the stronger the SN\nfeedback effects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Apr 2008 21:25:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Jul 2008 07:51:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
